Technology and network solutions company Parallel Wireless believes Long Term Evolution (LTE) technology should be considered a frontrunner in addressing safety, efficiency and productivity in underground mining. New-age LTE technology is set to outpace legacy communications systems like land mobile radio (LMR), as mining companies look to use the technology to streamline their operations and enhance the safety of the mines, Africa sales director Lux Maharaj tells Sascha Solomons. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 7 2018. It will be published online on the 23rd August 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy